Print Environment Variables :
Create a pod which print Greetings -->

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
YAML
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: print-envars-greeting            # Pod name
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never                   # Prevent restart / CrashLoopBackOff
  containers:
  - name: print-env-container            # Container name
    image: bash                          # Using bash image
    env:                                 # Environment variables
    - name: GREETING
      value: "Welcome to"
    - name: COMPANY
      value: "Nautilus"
    - name: GROUP
      value: "Datacenter"
    command: ["/bin/sh", "-c", 'echo "$(GREETING) $(COMPANY) $(GROUP)"']
   

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Output:
thor@jumphost ~$ kubectl logs -f print-envars-greeting 
Welcome to Nautilus Datacenter

----------------------------------------------------DONE-------------------------------------------------------------
